 joined to the negotiations between the Holy See and the Kádár regime: during the Council Hungary became the experimental laboratory of the Vatican's new eastern policy. Was it a Vatican decision or a Soviet instruction? Fejérdy suggests that it was a decision of the Holy See.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aChurch and statezHungaryxHistoryy20th century. 0aCommunism and ChristianityxCatholic Church. 0aCommunism and ChristianityzHungary. 0aCommunism and Christianity--Hungary. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Catholic.2bisacsh  aCatholic Church, Cold War, Communism, Diplomacy, Foreign relations, Politics of religion, Vatican.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2017z978311078143440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633861431423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789633861431/original  a978-3-11-078143-4  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK